Package Automata.TwoDimentions.WW

Class WireWorld

  • java.lang.Object
    • Automata.Automaton
      • Automata.TwoDimentions.Automaton2Dim
        • Automata.TwoDimentions.WW.WireWorld
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    WireWorldGriddy, WireWorldNonGriddy

    public abstract class WireWorld
extends Automaton2Dim

This one's a base class for every WireWorld automaton. The constructor is here because the child classes
differs only by getChanges method.
(The same issue of constructor goes to some other automata base classes but it wasn't written there, my bad.)

The neighborhood's length given in the neighborhood shouldn't be different than 1,
because it's logical, wireworld is to simulate the world of electricity and
in wires the electrons travel through the whole way without any jumps.
Yet any length is allowed not to upset the experimenters.
(The same goes to the QuadLife but it's not written there. My bad.)
